article.headline: Santa Clara 87, Bethany, Calif. 57
article.story: SANTA CLARA, Calif. -- Kevin Foster scored 19 points, including six 3-pointers, to lead Santa Clara to an 87-57 victory over Bethany, Calif. on Monday night. Foster shot 6 for 12 from the field with all of his baskets coming from long distance. He also made 1 of 3 from the free-throw line. Marc Trasolini added 15 points and a team-high seven rebounds for the Broncos (9-7). Santa Clara finished with 47.8 percent shooting from the field, including 55.2 percent in the first half. The Broncos led by as many as 35 points late in the game. Evan Fletscher led the Bruins (0-13) with 18 points while Marqus Crawford added 17 and Milton Brown scored 11.
